The paper proposes a clustering algorithm that utilizes multiple datasets with different types of features, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The approach involves completing the kernel matrices of incomplete datasets and optimizing the alignment of shared instances. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
